
** ISO

  mount -o loop <file>.iso /mnt

** DVDROM on Redhat

  mount /dev/dvd /mnt


** Bind

  - *bind* allows to rebind parts of the file hierarchy somewhere else.

  <example>
  # mount --bind /O1/home /home
  </example>

  - *bind* in /etc/fstab

  <pre>
  <verbatim>
  --- /etc/fstab ---
  /O1/home	/home	none	bind	0 0
  </verbatim>
  </pre>

** Windows-Mount


  - mount -t cifs -o user=maierha,domain=dom_mediasat  \
                     172.17.136.46:/jeder /mnt/jeder
